sourcesContent:
import { Project, Skill, Experience, Education } from '../types';

export const personalInfo = {
  name: "Conor Van Bibber",
  title: "Electrical Engineer",
  subtitle: "RF/Microwave Engineer & Hardware Designer",
  email: "cvanbibber@berkeley.edu",
  phone: "+1 (XXX) XXX-XXXX", // Update with actual phone
  location: "Berkeley, CA",
  linkedin: "https://linkedin.com/in/conor-van-bibber",
  github: "https://github.com/cvanbibber",
  website: "https://cvanbibber.github.io",
  bio: "Passionate electrical engineer specializing in RF/microwave design, antenna systems, and electromagnetic simulation. Experienced in both hardware design and software development with a focus on creating innovative solutions for complex engineering challenges."
};

export const skills: Skill[] = [
  // Programming
  { name: "Python", category: "programming", proficiency: 5, icon: "/skills/python.png" },
  { name: "C++", category: "programming", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/c++.png" },
  { name: "MATLAB", category: "programming", proficiency: 5, icon: "/skills/matlab.png" },
  
  // Hardware Design
  { name: "Altium Designer", category: "hardware", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/altium.png" },
  { name: "KiCad", category: "hardware", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/kicad.png" },
  
  // CAD/Mechanical
  { name: "SolidWorks", category: "software", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/solidworks.png" },
  { name: "Fusion 360", category: "software", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/fusion.png" },
  
  // Analysis Software
  { name: "ANSYS HFSS", category: "analysis", proficiency: 5, icon: "/skills/hfss.png" },
  { name: "ANSYS Maxwell", category: "analysis", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/maxwell.png" },
  { name: "ANSYS Fluent", category: "analysis", proficiency: 3, icon: "/skills/ansysfluent.png" },
  { name: "OpenFOAM", category: "analysis", proficiency: 3, icon: "/skills/openfoam.png" },
  
  // Manufacturing
  { name: "3D Printing", category: "hardware", proficiency: 5, icon: "/skills/3dprint.png" },
  { name: "CNC Machining", category: "hardware", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/cnc.png" },
  { name: "Laser Cutting", category: "hardware", proficiency: 4, icon: "/skills/lasercut.png" },
  { name: "Lathe Operation", category: "hardware", proficiency: 3, icon: "/skills/lathe.png" }
];

export const experiences: Experience[] = [
  {
    id: "exp-1",
    title: "RF Engineer Intern",
    company: "Tech Company", // Update with actual company
    location: "San Francisco, CA",
    startDate: "2023-06",
    endDate: "2023-08",
    description: [
      "Designed and simulated antenna arrays for 5G applications using ANSYS HFSS",
      "Developed Python scripts for automated electromagnetic analysis and optimization",
      "Collaborated with cross-functional teams to integrate RF solutions into product designs",
      "Performed measurements and validation of prototype antenna systems"
    ],
    technologies: ["ANSYS HFSS", "Python", "RF Design", "Antenna Arrays", "5G"]
  },
  // Add more experiences as needed
];

export const education: Education[] = [
  {
    id: "edu-1",
    degree: "Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering",
    institution: "University of California, Berkeley",
    location: "Berkeley, CA",
    startDate: "2020-08",
    endDate: "2024-05", // Update as needed
    gpa: "3.8/4.0", // Update with actual GPA
    achievements: [
      "Dean's List (multiple semesters)",
      "IEEE Student Member",
      "Senior Design Project: [Project Name]",
      "Relevant Coursework: Electromagnetics, RF Circuits, Antenna Theory, Signal Processing"
    ]
  }
];

export const projects: Project[] = [
  {
    id: "proj-1",
    title: "Phased Array Antenna Design",
    description: "Design and simulation of a 4x4 phased array antenna for beamforming applications",
    longDescription: "Comprehensive design of a 4x4 phased array antenna system with electronic beam steering capabilities. The project involved electromagnetic simulation, optimization for specific frequency bands, and prototype fabrication and testing.",
    technologies: ["ANSYS HFSS", "RF Design", "Antenna Theory", "Python", "MATLAB"],
    images: ["/projects/phased-array/main.jpg", "/projects/phased-array/simulation.jpg"],
    featured: true,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2024-03",
    status: "completed",
    demoUrl: "",
    githubUrl: ""
  },
  {
    id: "proj-2",
    title: "RF Power Amplifier Design",
    description: "High-efficiency class-E power amplifier for wireless communication systems",
    longDescription: "Design and implementation of a high-efficiency class-E power amplifier optimized for wireless communication applications. Includes circuit design, PCB layout, and comprehensive performance analysis.",
    technologies: ["Altium Designer", "RF Design", "Power Electronics", "Circuit Simulation"],
    images: ["/projects/power-amp/pcb.jpg", "/projects/power-amp/schematic.jpg"],
    featured: true,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2024-01",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "proj-3",
    title: "Electromagnetic Simulation Toolkit",
    description: "Python toolkit for automated electromagnetic analysis and visualization",
    longDescription: "Comprehensive Python toolkit that automates various electromagnetic simulation tasks, including field visualization, parameter sweeps, and optimization routines. Integrates with ANSYS HFSS and other simulation tools.",
    technologies: ["Python", "ANSYS HFSS", "Matplotlib", "NumPy", "SciPy"],
    images: ["/projects/em-toolkit/gui.jpg", "/projects/em-toolkit/results.jpg"],
    featured: true,
    category: "software",
    date: "2023-11",
    status: "completed",
    githubUrl: "https://github.com/cvanbibber/em-toolkit"
  },
  {
    id: "proj-4",
    title: "IoT Sensor Network",
    description: "Wireless sensor network for environmental monitoring with custom PCB design",
    longDescription: "Complete IoT solution including custom PCB design, embedded firmware, and cloud-based data visualization. The system monitors temperature, humidity, and air quality across multiple locations.",
    technologies: ["KiCad", "ESP32", "C++", "IoT", "PCB Design"],
    images: ["/projects/iot-sensors/pcb.jpg", "/projects/iot-sensors/deployment.jpg"],
    featured: false,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2023-09",
    status: "completed"
  }
];

export const featuredProjects = projects.filter(project => project.featured);
